properties.headline: ALPINE CONDITIONS - KOSCIUSZKO NATIONAL PARK Kosciuszko Road
properties.otherAdvice:
Beyond Perisher, The road is closed.

Guthega Rd: Chains are required from the Kosciuszko Rd entry to the resort.

The following road closures will be in effect throughout the winter period:
- Kosciuszko Rd will be closed between Perisher and Charlotte Pass.
- Link Rd will be closed between Guthega and Smiggin Holes.

Chains must be carried in Kosciuszko National Park in winter (4WDs exempt). All motorists should be prepared and equipped for sudden changes in road and weather conditions in Alpine areas.

properties.headline: ALPINE CONDITIONS - BOGAN SHIRE COUNCIL Local roads
properties.otherAdvice:
Many unsealed roads across Bogan Shire are now closed to all vehicles.

Local roads in the Bogan Shire Council area may be closed due to flooding or affected by adverse weather. For further information, visit the council's website or contact Bogan Shire Council on (02) 6835 9000.

properties.headline: ALPINE CONDITIONS - KOSCIUSZKO NATIONAL PARK Alpine Way
properties.otherAdvice:
Road open to Thredbo.

Between Khancoban (Murray 1 Power Station) and Thredbo, the road is closed due to heavy snow and fallen trees.

Motorists are also advised to be prepared and equipped for sudden changes in road and weather conditions in alpine areas.

properties.headline: ALPINE CONDITIONS - KOSCIUSZKO NATIONAL PARK Snowy Mountains Highway
properties.otherAdvice:

Kings Cross Rd will be closed throughout the winter period.

Chains must be carried in Kosciuszko National Park in winter (4WDs exempt). 

All drivers should be prepared and equipped for sudden changes in road and weather conditions in Alpine areas.

ALPINE CONDITIONS - ORANGE CITY COUNCIL Local roads
properties.adviceB: Delay your journey; Plan your journey
properties.otherAdvice:
Local roads throughout Orange are impacted by heavy snowfall and reduced visibility. For further information, contact the council via their website or 02 6393 8000.

The following roads are closed:
- Pinnacle Rd at Shiralee Rd.
- Canobolas Rd between Pinnacle Rd and Lake Canobolas Rd.

Motorists are advised to avoid unnecessary travel in the area due to snow and ice affecting a number of roads. Motorists needing to travel should exercise extreme caution, reduce speed and be prepared for conditions to change quickly.

properties.headline: ALPINE CONDITIONS Ice - GLEN INNES TO GUYRA New England Highway between Glen Legh Road, Glen Innes AND Guyra
properties.adviceB: Avoid the area; Delay your journey
properties.otherAdvice: Ice and adverse weather conditions are limiting visibility.
properties.diversions:
Motorists who must travel can consider using the following as an alternative route.

Northbound: From Armidale, take Waterfall Way to Raleigh, then Pacific Hwy to South Grafton then Big River Way and Gwydir Hwy to return to Glen Innes.

Southbound: From Glen Innes, take Gwydir Hwy to South Grafton, then Big River Way and Pacific Hwy to Raleigh, then Waterfall Way.

This alternative route adds around 4 hours travel time.
